            <h3>DEPARTMENT OF ELECTRICAL ENGINEERING</h3>
            <p>
                The Department of Electrical Engineering at <strong> Government Polytechnic Siwan</strong> is a dynamic and future-oriented academic department dedicated to producing competent, skilled, and industry-ready diploma engineers. The department offers a <strong>Diploma in Electrical Engineering,</strong> a programme designed to meet the growing demand for technically proficient professionals in the power, energy, automation, and electrical services sectors.
            </p>
            <p>
                Electrical Engineering is a core engineering discipline that underpins modern infrastructure, industry, and technological advancement. In recognition of its critical importance, the department delivers an outcome-based and industry-aligned curriculum that blends strong theoretical foundations with extensive practical exposure. The programme covers essential domains such as electrical circuits, electrical machines, power generation, transmission and distribution, control systems, power electronics, renewable energy systems, estimation and costing, and electrical safety practices.
            </p>
            <p>
                The department is strengthened by a team of well-qualified, experienced, and dedicated faculty members who are deeply committed to academic excellence and student development. Innovative teaching–learning practices, laboratory-based instruction, project work, industrial visits, and expert interactions are integral to the pedagogical approach. Faculty members mentor students to develop analytical thinking, problem-solving abilities, and professional competence.
            </p>
            <p>
                Well-equipped laboratories serve as the cornerstone of practical training, providing students with hands-on experience in operating electrical machines, testing equipment, wiring systems, control panels, and modern electrical tools. Special emphasis is placed on safety standards, precision, discipline, and adherence to industry norms, ensuring students are well-prepared for real-world working environments.
            </p>
            <p>
                The Department of Electrical Engineering maintains close coordination with industry and the institute’s Training & Placement Cell to facilitate industrial training, internships, and placement opportunities. Graduates of the programme find employment across a wide spectrum of sectors, including power utilities, manufacturing industries, construction and infrastructure projects, renewable energy companies, automation firms, and public sector undertakings. The programme also provides a strong foundation for students aspiring to pursue higher education through lateral entry into engineering degree programmes.
            </p>
            <p>
                Beyond academics, the department actively encourages student participation in co-curricular and extracurricular activities, skill development initiatives, innovation challenges, and community outreach programmes. These engagements foster leadership qualities, teamwork, communication skills, and a sense of social responsibility.
            </p>
            <p>
                With a strong focus on academic rigor, practical competence, employability, and ethical values, the Department of Electrical Engineering at Government Polytechnic Siwan is committed to shaping technically sound, socially responsible, and future-ready electrical engineering professionals who can contribute meaningfully to national development.
            </p>
            <h4>VISION OF THE DEPARTMENT</h4>
            <p>
                To emerge as a Centre of Excellence in Diploma-level Electrical Engineering education, nurturing competent, ethical, and industry-ready electrical professionals through performance-oriented learning, multidisciplinary exposure, innovation, and sustainable practices, aligned with contemporary national educational reforms, and contributing meaningfully to societal and national development.
            </p>
            <h4>MISSION OF THE DEPARTMENT </h4>
